## 3. Design Variety Without Changing Assets

You CAN create visual variety while keeping original assets by:

### Layout Variations
- Change photo position (left vs right side)
- Change text position and hierarchy
- Vary frame shapes (trapezoid vs angular vs geometric)
- Adjust spacing and margins

### Color Variations (Background)
- Switch between dark navy blue (#1a3a7a) and variations (#1a2a5a, #2a1a4a)
- Keep logo and photo colors UNCHANGED
- Adjust accent colors within professional range (gold #d4af37 - #ffd700)

### Compositional Changes
- Mirror layout for different lessons
- Adjust text size and positioning
- Create different visual rhythms
- Use different decorative divider styles (lines, ornaments, etc.)

### Text Treatment
- Different font sizing hierarchy
- Varied line breaks and spacing
- Different ordering of elements
- Multiple layout templates

---

## 4. What Constitutes "Original Asset"

### ✅ Original Logo
- The exact file: `Screenshot1-b89ff80f-9fce-4c13-968f-f20380b3a2ec.png`
- Not a description or artistic interpretation
- Not a "similar looking" logo

### ✅ Original Photos
- The five provided Dmitry Kalashnik photos
- Not descriptions like "man in blue shirt"
- Not reference images to generate from
- Not AI interpretations of "scholar studying Torah"

### ❌ Generated Assets
- AI-generated logos (even if similar)
- AI-generated faces (even if similar to real person)
- Composite images with generated elements
- Descriptions used to generate images

